commitResults.messageBody: Created classes and packages for the project
Include flags for drug and patient
Implemented ActiveIngredient, Direction, Drug, UniqueDrugList classes

Change Purpose to Set<Purpose> since a drug can often treat multiple
symptoms

Updated Parser hierarchy such that the top level parser is now
CareFlowParser, which distributes tasks to GeneralParser/PatientParser/
DrugParser. The 3 secondary parsers then switch to each specific command
parsers.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adapt Model and Logic for CareFlow
commitResults.messageBody:
Created DrugInventory class which implements ReadOnlyDrugInventory to
handle drug related operations.
Created PatientRecord class which implements ReadOnlyPatientRecord to
handle patient related operations.
Created ClearCommand for both Patient and Drug.
Implemented CareFlow which dispatches patient and drug related operations
to PatientRecord and DrugInventory respectively.
Implemented CareFlowModel and CareFlowModelManager.
Implemented CareFlowLogic and CareFlowLogicManager.
Changed code which uses the old logic/model to use our CareFlow version,
there can be some omissions.
Other changes are made to avoid errors. (e.g. execute#Command now takes
CareFlowModel as argument, so addressBook commands are no longer working,
I commented out the @Override annotation such that the code still
compiles).

commitResults.messageTitle: Update method signature of commands to accept CareFlowModel

commitResults.messageBody:
Removed outdated files to avoid confusion. Code which references these
classes are commented out such that the file still compiles. Commented
code are mainly related to storage, which will be implemented later.

Created DrugInventoryStorage, PatientRecordStorage, CareFlowStorage,
JsonDrugInventoryStorage, JsonPatientRecordStorage, CareFlowStorageManager
classes for the storage of CareFlow data

Adapted Storage component for CareFlow by implementing:
1. JsonSerializablePatientRecord
2. JsonSerializableDrugInventory
3. JsonPatientRecordStorage
4. JsonDrugInventoryStorage
5. JsonAdaptedPatient

Modified preferences.json to allowing loading of data from:
`data/patientRecord.json` and `data/drugInventory.json`

Adapted UI implementation for the presentation of patient and drug data
by implementing:
1. DrugCard
2. PatientCard
3. DrugListCard.fxml
4. PatientlistCard.fxml
5. StatusBarFooter

Prepared sample data for first time users by modifying:
1. SampleDateUtil: added getSamplePatients() and getSampleDrugs() methods
by creating sample patients and sample drugs.

Removed obsolete addressBook classes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update UI to enforce textWrap for long texts
Fix bug caused by optional fields inside patient
commitResults.messageBody:
- Addressed bug report: When adding new record for the first time, JSON
is created but the new data is not written.
	- Cause: Optional fields drugAllergy and EmergencyContact are not
	initialised inside the overloaded constructor, causing the
	getDrugAllergy() and getEmergencyContact() to produce
	NullPointerException when called by JsonAdaptedPerson#toModelType()
	which is in turn called by JsonSerializablePatientRecord constructor
	during storage.
- Edited JsonAdaptedPerson#toModelType() to handle the conversion of
null values for the two optional fields.

commitResults.messageTitle: Resolve inconsistency for drug update command structure
commitResults.messageBody:
- change command structure from: d update -tn TRADE_NAME -up AMOUNT to:
d update TRADE_NAME -by AMOUNT, such that:
	- the command structure resembles that of patient update command
	- -by flag is more intuitive than -up flag as -up can lead to
	confusions
- add OPERATION_TYPE to MESSAGE_USAGE for patient and drug commands such
that error message show a complete command structure.
	ie. previously: ... example: update Alex Yeoh... updated: p update...
